Product.modelDescription: Turn the urban landscape into a playground with Cannondale's Capo 2. The frame is made from Cannondale's CAAD5 aluminum with an aero aluminum fork that's stiff, light and durable, just what you need when sprinting for the light. Same goes for the wheels, they won't slow you down on climbs, and they'll stay true after bashing into a pothole or 2. For speed everywhere you go, you've got 46/18 gearing, not too big and not too small, and your rear hub is flippable, so you can switch it from fixie to a coasting singlespeed easily. Plus, the flat bars are narrow enough to squeeze you through that alley with the parked trucked and wide enough to crank on when rocking it uphill.

The Mountain Mirrycle Mirror quickly attaches to most any flat handlebar using the supplied wrench. Its convex mirror provides a wide field of view to help you clearly see approaching traffic. And the mirror head adjusts to your optimum viewing angle.
The Original Mirrycle Mirror fits older style brake levers which use non-aero cable routing, as shown in the photo.
The Incredibell XL is louder and a little larger, but with the same unique pivoting dinger that keeps it compact for fitting on packed handlebars.

Finding the perfect gift can be tough. Which is exactly why we offer gift certificates. They make great presents for relatives and friends, and are a fantastic way to thank someone special. They're always the right size and color, too. We can mail the certificate to you or the intended recipient. Just enter the appropriate address in the "Ship To" field during checkout. Gift certificates are for in-store redemption only.

Don't let the half-pint stature fool you, Mirrycle's little Incredibell Brass Solo packs the beautifully resonant ring of solid brass. Its compact size and pivoting ringer let you mount it just about anywhere on your handlebars. A flick of your finger and it rings clear for all to hear.
Mirrcyle's Incredibell Big Brass makes a dual-tone, melodic ring with the beautifully resonant ding of solid brass. Its compact size lets you mount it just about anywhere on your handlebars.
Mirrycle's Candibell is more than just a fun, compact bell. Not only does it come in five delicious candy colors (shown), it’s the loudest Incredibell of all.
The Mirrycle Jellibell is a fun way to let pedestrians and other riders know you're coming! The Jellibell has a see-through top so you can see the gears spin as it rings. It's weatherproof, too!
The Tube Trap secures your drinking tube to CamelBak's 3/4-inch shoulder straps to keep it within close proximity. It fits both insulated and regular delivery tubes.
